+++ b/replit.md
@@ -0,0 +1,123 @@
+# BYOA — Build Your Own Algorithm
+
+A personal knowledge archive inspired by mymind. Save articles, images, notes, links, and more into a searchable, AI-enriched card collection.
+
+## Architecture
+
+- **Framework**: RedwoodJS 8.9 (full-stack React + GraphQL)
+- **Frontend**: React 18 + Vite, served on port **5000** (host `0.0.0.0`)
+- **Backend API**: GraphQL Yoga server on port **8912** (localhost)
+- **Database**: PostgreSQL via Supabase (Prisma ORM)
+- **Auth**: Supabase Auth (email/password)
+- **Package manager**: Yarn 4 (via corepack) — use `corepack yarn` to run yarn commands
+
+## Key directories
+
+```
+api/
+  src/
+    functions/   — Serverless functions (capture, graphql, imageProxy)
+    services/    — Business logic (cards, spaces, search, export, …)
+    graphql/     — SDL type definitions
+    directives/  — GraphQL directives
+    lib/         — Shared API utilities
+  db/
+    schema.prisma — Prisma schema (PostgreSQL / Supabase)
+
+web/
+  src/
+    pages/       — Route-level page components
+    layouts/     — AppLayout, AuthLayout
+    components/  — Reusable UI components
+    lib/         — supabaseClient, graph, theme, hooks, …
+    auth.ts      — Supabase auth adapter for RedwoodJS
+```
+
+## Configuration
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `redwood.toml` | Ports (web=5000, api=8912), env var allowlist |
+| `web/vite.config.ts` | Vite config — `host: '0.0.0.0'`, `allowedHosts: 'all'` |
+| `.env.defaults` | Default env vars (SQLite fallback for DATABASE_URL) |
+| `.env.example` | Template for all required secrets |
+
+## Required environment variables
+
+Set these in the Replit Secrets panel before using the app:
+
+| Variable | Description |
+|----------|-------------|
+| `DATABASE_URL` | Supabase PostgreSQL connection string (pooled) |
+| `DIRECT_DATABASE_URL` | Supabase direct connection (for migrations) |
+| `REDWOOD_ENV_SUPABASE_URL` | Supabase project URL |
+| `REDWOOD_ENV_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Supabase anon/public key |
+| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Supabase service role key (API-side only) |
+
+Optional (for full feature set):
+- `R2_ENDPOINT`, `R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `R2_BUCKET_NAME` — Cloudflare R2 export storage
+- `REDWOOD_ENV_SENTRY_DSN` — Sentry error tracking
+- `REDWOOD_ENV_POSTHOG_KEY` — PostHog analytics
+- `REDWOOD_ENV_BYOA_SHORTCUT_URL` — iOS Shortcut download link
+
+## Running the app
+
+The workflow command is:
+```
+corepack yarn install && corepack yarn rw dev
+```
+
+This installs deps (idempotent after first run) and starts both the API and web dev servers.
+
+## Deployment
+
+Configured as `autoscale` deployment:
+- **Build**: `yarn rw build`
+- **Run**: `yarn rw serve`
+
+## Notable implementation details
+
+- `web/src/lib/supabaseClient.ts` — lazy Proxy pattern defers client init until first use, preventing a blank-screen crash when env vars are absent
+- `redwood.toml` — `browser.open = false` prevents auto-opening a browser tab in the Replit environment
+- The Supabase admin client on the API side silently skips init when `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` is absent (logged as a warning)
+
+## Graph UI — 3D renderer
+
+- `web/src/components/ThreeGraphRenderer/ThreeGraphRenderer.tsx` — Three.js renderer with:
+  - Quaternion trackball (Ken Shoemake arcball) — no gimbal lock; momentum spin decays at 0.92/frame
+  - Compass Rose (5 orientation presets, slerp animation) — always visible when the Three.js renderer is mounted (i.e. when `localDimension === '3d'`); no longer gated on an `is3D` sub-state
+  - Perspective camera only; orthographic fallback removed to simplify state
+- `web/src/components/GraphFilterPanel/GraphFilterPanel.tsx` — filter pill always at `top-[60px]` (a consistent second row below the `top-3` chrome); `sm:top-4` override removed to prevent overlap with the 2D/3D and Graph/List toggles
+
+## Design-system tests
+
+Spacing and token-usage enforcement tests (run with `yarn rw test web`):
+
+- `web/src/components/GraphFilterPanel/GraphFilterPanel.test.tsx` — verifies `top-[60px]`, `z-40`, CSS-variable colours, aria-labels, and live counters
+- `web/src/components/GraphDimensionToggle/GraphDimensionToggle.test.tsx` — verifies ≥ 44 px touch targets, CSS-variable colours, ARIA radiogroup semantics, and interaction guard
+
+## Mobile — Expo app (in progress)
+
+`mobile/` contains the Expo Router scaffold for the native BYOA app.
+It shares the same RedwoodJS GraphQL backend via `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL`.
+
+Key files:
+| Path | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `mobile/app.json` | Expo config (slug `byoa-mobile`, bundle `com.byoa.mobile`) |
+| `mobile/constants/colors.ts` | BYOA colour tokens synced from `web/.../byoa.json` |
+| `mobile/hooks/useColors.ts` | Dark-mode-aware colour hook |
+| `mobile/lib/graphql.ts` | Typed GraphQL fetch client pointing to Redwood API |
+| `mobile/lib/authMachine.ts` | XState v5 auth state machine (idle → checking → authenticated) |
+| `mobile/contexts/AuthContext.tsx` | React context wrapping the auth machine + SecureStore persistence |
+| `mobile/app/_layout.tsx` | Root layout: QueryClient, SafeAreaProvider, AuthProvider, KeyboardProvider |
+| `mobile/app/(tabs)/feed.tsx` | Card feed from GraphQL, pull-to-refresh |
+| `mobile/app/(tabs)/graph.tsx` | WebView bridge to the web 3D graph (native Three.js planned) |
+| `mobile/app/(tabs)/settings.tsx` | Profile & sign-out |
+| `mobile/app/login.tsx` | Email/password sign-in screen |
+
+To start the mobile app (once deps are installed):
+```
+cd mobile && npx expo start --port 8081
+```
+Set `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL` in `mobile/.env` to point at the running RedwoodJS server.
